now install and remove packages works perfectly.\r\n\r\nWith the help of [richard](http://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/) by [email](http://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/packagekit/2008-November/003994.html)\r\n\r\ni can solve problems:\r\n\r\n    pkcon search name <app>\r\n    pkcon refresh\r\n    pkcon resolve <app>\r\n    pkcon install <app>\r\n    pkcon remove <app>\r\n\r\nnext the update-system, and get-updates. more info <http://wiki.foresightlinux.org/display/DEV/packagekit+devel+page>\r\n\r\nWell today a friend contact me to a person on Cancun Qroo (A great tourist Paradise) and gime a immediately Job sooo on thurday im travel to cancun for work about a 1.5 Month.  For what more like development python. I will be a leader of 3 coders on a started project.  i hope have time to development packagekit.','packagekit-improvements-and-new-job'),(65,'PackageKit now is FIXED','2008-11-18 01:46:53','<center>\r\n![packagekit 0.3.11](http://img362.imageshack.us/img362/892/pantallazoacercadegpkapeh3.png)\r\n</center>\r\n\r\nIm very happy because the packagekit its fixed. We are working with a old version (0.3.4) ( Crash the fl philosophy )  \r\nNow im finish fixing backend now works good with 0.3.11  (the [unreleased version](http://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/packagekit/2008-November/004016.html) ) ooooh ciiiii .\r\n\r\nWell free feel for test and report bugs   \r\n\r\n`sudo conary update {PackageKit,gnome-packagekit}=@fl:2-devel`\r\n\r\nThe unique improvement what i can do its: Faster refresh cache.\r\n\r\ncommands:\r\n\r\n    :::bash\r\n    pkcon search name <app>\r\n    pkcon refresh\r\n    pkcon resolve <app>\r\n    pkcon install <app>\r\n    pkcon remove <app>\r\n    pkcon get-details\r\n    pkcon update system\r\n    pkcon get-files <app>\r\n    pkcon get-updates <app>\r\n    pkcon get-details <app>\r\n    pkcon get-update-details <app>\r\n\r\nBut from now. Only we seen improvements and new features. ','packagekit-now-fixed'),(66,'packagekit tip','2008-11-19 00:13: