commands on remote servers. With it you can automate updates/softwares and others stuff. very Usefull.\r\n\r\nexample:   \r\n\r\n     :::python\r\n     set(\r\n         project = \'awesome-app\',\r\n         fab_hosts = [\'n1.cluster.com\', \'n2.cluster.com\'],\r\n      )\r\n     def deploy():\r\n        \"Build the project and deploy it to a specified environment.\"\r\n         local(\'mvn package\')\r\n         put(\'target/$(project).war\', \'$(project).war\')\r\n         put(\'install-script.sh\', \'install-script.sh\')\r\n         sudo(\'install-script.sh\')','fabric-pythonic-tool-deployment'),(80,'stream/share music video to xbox360 and ps3','2009-01-20 12:48:03','My friend [TForsman](http://www.foresightlinux.se/blog) package the [ushare](http://ushare.geexbox.org/) app.\r\n\r\nThis its a software what can be recognized by xbox360 and PS3 consoles. for stream files. Soo this how it works its on wiki\r\n\r\n[https://wiki.foresightlinux.org/display/docs/Stream+music+and+videos+with+xbox+360+and+PS3](https://wiki.foresightlinux.org/display/docs/Stream+music+and+videos+with+xbox+360+and+PS3)','streamshare-music-video-xbox360-and-ps3'),(81,'match url /foo/2009-01-01/','2009-01-22 14:32:28','on a django how match a date string like 2009-01-01 with this:\r\n\r\n    :::python    \r\n    (r\'^reportes/(?P<fecha>\\d+-\\d+-\\d+)/$\',\'pos.boutiques.views.report\'),\r\n\r\ntime left on it: 30 min.\r\n\r\nDanmit im need re-learn regex of python','match-url-foo2009-01-01'),(82,'anti-piratas','2009-01-22 16:00:34','<img src=\"http://linuxhispano.net/tira/piratas.png\">','anti-piratas'),(83,'pyExcelerator making xls files with python','2009-01-26 12:52:04','This week ended. Im use this lib its called funny pyExcelerator ( remember me terminator movie).\r\n\r\nIts a python module for make files compatibles with MS excel Office.\r\n\r\nIm try it and can open files with Office 2007, Mac Office and Openoffice. This solve my problems with endusers what a need a reports in excel.\r\n\r\nhere a example:\r\n\r\n    :::python\r\n    from pyExcelerator import *\r\n    \r\n    w = Workbook()\r\n    ws = w.add_sheet(\'Hey, Dude\')\r\n    \r\n    ws.write(0, 0, 1)\r\n    ws.write(1, 0, 1.23)\r\n    ws.write(2, 0, 12345678)\r\n    ws.write(3, 0, 123456.78)\r\n    \r\n    ws.write(0, 1, -1)\r\n    ws.write(1, 1, -1.23)\r\n    ws.write(2, 1, -12345678)\r\n    ws.write(3, 1, -123456.78)\r\n    \r\n    ws.write(0, 2, -17867868678687.0)\r\n    ws.write(1, 2, -1.23e-5)\r\n    ws.write(2, 2, -12345678.90780980)\r\n    ws.write(3, 2, -123456.78)\r\n    \r\n    w.save(\'numbers.xls\')\r\n\r\nthe better of that module its not have deps. so not need a openoffice core/lib for used it.   \r\n\r\n$ yolk -S name=pyExcelerator -M pyExcelerator  \r\nauthor: Roman V. Kiseliov   \r\nauthor_email: roman@kiseliov.ru  \r\ndownload_url: http://www.sourceforge.net/projects/pyexcelerator  \r\nplatform: Platform-independent  \r\nversion: 0.6.0a  \r\n','pyexcelerator-making-xls-files-python'),(84,'guess what programming language  control this robots','2009-01-29 12:45:58','![robot](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_1srVB7Ihd-8/SX_S-hJqsXI/AAAAAAAAAIQ/FL1vuIkfRJE/s320/IMG_1357.JPG)\r\n\r\n![robot2](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_1srVB7Ihd-8/SYBLjY7PfiI/AAAAAAAAAIY/c3jsLn8TmrE/s320/IMG_1358.JPG)\r\n\r\nANSWER: http://entitycrisis.blogspot.com/2009/01/giant-python-powered-robots.html','guess-what-programming-language-control-robots'),(85,'kde4.2 on foresightlinux','2009-01-30 11:35:06','`sudo conary update group-kde4=kde.rpath.org@fl:2-kde4.2-devel`\r\n\r\nand it download all requires to use kde4.2.\r\n\r\nKde 4.2 its not official of Foresight so if you have question about it. you can Visit:\r\n\r\nforesight-kde channel on irc.freenode.org and ask for how use it.\r\n\r\nupdate:\r\n*** Reading foresight channel you must migrate your foresight system to 2-qa for install kde4.2 because deps of python2.6 and python2.6 for now its on 2-qa branch and 2-devel','kde42-foresightlinux'),(86,'playing with conary public api','2009-02-02 01:45:23','Im working with conary backend of PackageKit, i can do a some hacks implements the new Cache.\r\nSome examples what i do:\r\n\r\nGet the MetaData Info from some package:\r\n\r\n    :::python\r\n    from conary.conaryclient import ConaryClient\r\n    cli = ConaryClient()\r\n    \r\n    trove_list  =  cli.db.getTroveList(\"gimp\")\r\n    for trove in trove_list:\r\n        print \"Info about: %s \"% trove.getName()\r\n        meta_dict = trove.getAllMetadataItems()[0]\r\n        for key in meta_dict.keys():\r\n            m = getattr(meta_dict,key)\r\n            print \"%s : %s\" %(key, m() )\r\n\r\nOutput:   \r\n\r\n    :::bash\r\n    [zodman@cosmogirl tests]$ python conaryclient.py \r\n    Info about: gimp \r\n    shortDesc : Image Editor\r\n    longDesc : Create images and edit photographs\r\n    categories : [\'2DGraphics\', \'GTK\', \'Graphics\', \'RasterGraphics\']\r\n\r\n\r\nCool :) This output its similar a  \r\n\r\n`$ conary q gimp --info`\r\n\r\n[zodman@cosmogirl tests]$ conary q gimp --info  \r\nName      : gimp               Build time: Tue Sep 16 11:17:33 2008  \r\nVersion   : 2.4.6-0.2-1        Label     : foresight.rpath.org@fl:2  \r\nSize      : 53372245            \r\nPinned    : False  \r\nFlavor    : is: x86             \r\nCategory  : 2DGraphics  \r\nCategory  : GTK  \r\nCategory  : Graphics  \r\nCategory  : RasterGraphics  \r\nSummary   : Image Editor  \r\nDescription:   \r\n    Create images and edit photographs  \r\n\r\n','playing-conary-public-api'),(87,'conarylib using the conary public api','2009-02-03 23:18:39','Doing the hacking of packagekit im reading the code from conaryBackend.py conaryFilter.py Cache.py\r\n\r\nIm very lost following the code so im decide make more modular can i posible to do.\r\n\r\nBTW im not found some code example or blogpost about how to use the conary public api. Im have to read the code from /usr/bin/conary file. And get some details of conary api.\r\n\r\nOnly the little help of mkj. I can do a equal of \"conary q\" and \"conary rq\"\r\n\r\nSo im decide to make a small module for basic task ( what can Improvement the packagekit) of conary api. Commands line equal with use the cli conary.\r\n\r\nSo get check the code:\r\n\r\n[http://github.com/zodman/conary-lib/](http://github.com/zodman/conary-lib/)\r\n','conarylib-using-conary-public-api'),(88,'Update a app with conary-lib','2009-02-05 02:15:37','Yeah im add a method for a simple:  conary update app\\<\\=repo\\@tag\\:label\\> \r\n\r\nReading the [documentation][2] and seen some code im understand some things....\r\n\r\n* For conary update a package ( called installing a package) need to create a Job\r\n* With this job its a empty for begining. You must attach some task like (Update)\r\n* If job created the update must Apply for install it.\r\n* for update a package needs be a ChangeSpec Format:   \r\n   (troveName, (oldVersionSpec, oldFlavor), (newVersionSpec, newFlavor)\r\n* conary.conary.ConaryClient its the base of conary Structure on Conary API.\r\n\r\nFrom command line:  \r\n\r\n    :::sh\r\n    [zodman@cosmogirl conary-lib]$ conary q iftop\r\n    iftop was not found\r\n    [zodman@cosmogirl conary-lib]$ sudo python conarypk.py\r\n    Update Success of iftop=/zodyrepo.rpath.org@rpl:devel/0.17-3-1\r\n    [zodman@cosmogirl conary-lib]$ conary q iftop --labels\r\n    iftop=zodyrepo.rpath.org@rpl:devel/0.17-3-1\r\n\r\nthe new method:\r\n\r\n    :::python\r\n    def update(self, name, installLabel= None):\r\n            cli = self.cli\r\n            #get a trove\r\n            troves = self.request_query(name, installLabel)\r\n            for trove in troves:\r\n                trovespec =  self.trove_to_spec( trove )\r\n            try:\r\n                # create a Job\r\n                job = cli.newUpdateJob()\r\n                # Add Update task to Job\r\n                cli.prepareUpdateJob(job, cmdline.parseChangeList(trovespec))\r\n                # Apply the Job\r\n                cli.applyUpdateJob(job)\r\n                # im rulz\r\n                return \"Update Success of %s\" %  trovespec\r\n            except NoNewTrovesError:\r\n                return \"no new Troves Found by %s \" % trovespec\r\n        \r\n        def trove_to_spec(self, trove ):\r\n            return cmdline.toTroveSpec( trove[0], str(trove[1]), None)\r\n\r\n    \r\nUsing [conary-lib][1]:\r\n\r\n        :::python\r\n        conary = ConaryPk()\r\n        print conary.update(\"iftop\",\"zodyrepo.rpath.org@rpl:devel\")\r\n\r\n[1]: http://github.com/zodman/conary-lib/blob/992befb5d82abafab83092e764caa3f1df054182/conarypk.py\r\n[2]: http://cvs.rpath.com/conary-docs','conary-api-update-app-conary-lib'),(89,'conary-lib update and PackageKit hacking','2009-02-09 01:02:24','conary-lib:\r\n\r\nIm hack the lib and add the remove method what as the same of update but a little change add a \"-\" after the spec string for when do a update have translated to:\r\n\r\n` $ conary update -gimp=mylabel.rpath.org@rpl:devel `\r\n\r\nwhats as the same of doing \r\n\r\n`$ conary erase gimp`\r\n\r\nIm understand this rapid because [Mark__T](http://marktmisc.blogspot.com/) show me that time ago.\r\nSo its be easy to implement.\r\n\r\nOther command its get  a metadata info from a package.\r\n\r\n        :::python\r\n        def get_metadata( self, name , installLabel = None):\r\n            troveTuple = self.request_query( name, installLabel )\r\n            repos = self._get_repos()\r\n            troves = repos.getTroves(troveTuple)\r\n            metadata = None\r\n            for trove in troves:\r\n                if trove:\r\n                    metadata = trove.getMetadata()\r\n            return metadata\r\n\r\nFor get:\r\n\r\n        :::python\r\n        conary = conaryPK\r\n        print conary.get_metadata(\"christine\",\'zodyrepo.rpath.org@rpl:devel\')\r\n        # output: {\'bibliography\': None, \'language\': None, \'url\': None, \'notes\': None, \'crypto\': None,\r\n        \'licenses\': None, \'keyValue\': None, \'shortDesc\': \'Christine Media Player\', \'longDesc\': \'Gstreamer Based Media Player\',\r\n         \'categories\': [\'Application\', \'AudioVideo\', \'GTK\']}\r\n\r\n\r\nPackageKit:\r\n\r\nIm work on packagekit. here the Update: [http://lists.rpath.org/pipermail/foresight-devel/2009-February/000720.html](http://lists.rpath.org/pipermail/foresight-devel/2009-February/000720.html)\r\n','conary-lib-update-and-packagekit-hacking'),(90,'PackageKit Release 4.4','2009-02-23 10:08:24','[PackageKit release](http://cgit.freedesktop.org/packagekit/tree/NEWS) yeah!!!\r\n\r\n\r\nBut why its  important ... \r\n\r\nWell this its my first official contrib to FLOSS. Im only hacks some libs, or make small patches, not really somelike bigger like fix a Backend and Rewrite/Implement new features.\r\n\r\nSo i give love to packagekit. By supporting the conary backend.\r\n\r\nNow im listened [monkey contribs of packagekit](http://packagekit.org/pk-authors.html) ( im at last ).\r\n\r\nSo what happen with Packagekit..... \r\nwell foresight pass from this:\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n![oldpackagekit](http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3288/3143453953_0d0e5f88a4.jpg)\r\nOLD\r\n</center>\r\nTo this:  \r\n<center>\r\n<a href=\"http://twitpic.com/1ngfo\" title=\"the new PackageKit For Foresight on TwitPic\"><img src=\"http://twitpic.com/show/thumb/1ngfo.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" alt=\"the new PackageKit For Foresight on TwitPic\"></a>  \r\nNEW\r\n</center>\r\n\r\nNew Features:\r\n\r\n conary:Update the Cache with a NewCache.  \r\n conary:Add more support for reading metadata info.  \r\n conary:Support search [name|group|details].  \r\n conary:Packages Browsing.  \r\n conary:Add percent to install/remove/get-updates/update-system.   \r\n\r\nYes We have a Packages Browsing ... this make a step less for [kick ass Desktop](https://issues.foresightlinux.org/browse/FL-1380). The issue its not done, because need some tunnings and updates.\r\n\r\nOther thing its new code new bugs im invite to all Foresight\'ers to get PackageKit from 2-devel tag an test it:\r\n\r\n` sudo conary update {PackageKit,gnome-packagekit}=@fl:2-devel`\r\n\r\nAnd report bugs to me or on [FITS](http:://issues.foresightlinux.org).\r\n\r\nOk we have packages Browsing But not have  items populate with metadata. So our Browsing are Poor .\r\n\r\nAlthough need a new ideas comes for Populate data what i like. That to be a mark for foresight from other distros..( donophin have a great Idea )  \r\n\r\nIt can be some like [slackfind](http://slackfind.net/en), [AUR](http://aur.archlinux.org/), [debian mentor.](http://mentors.debian.net/cgi-bin/welcome)\r\n\r\nWell new Stuff come as [kenvandine](http://blogs.gnome.org/kenvandine/) said _we’ll kick ass in 2009_','packagekit-release-44'),(91,'enlightenment on foresight','2009-02-27 01:52:49','e17 its on fl repos ....\r\n\r\n`sudo conary update enlightenment`\r\n\r\nIts beauty!!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://img27.imageshack.us/img27/4130/e17.png\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://img27.imageshack.us/img27/4130/e17.th.png\" border=\"0\"  /></a>','enlightenment-foresight'),(92,'saint seiya the anime .. im loved!','2009-02-27 18:49:40','im very excited because im know about the new anime serie of saint seiya.\r\n\r\nSaint Seiya - The lost canvas ...\r\n\r\n![saint-seiya](http://img264.imageshack.us/img264/4885/3297481126780d3033a0o.jpg)\r\n\r\nAnd the new disc of make-up with the main themes of Saint Seiya.\r\n\r\n<object width=\"425\" height=\"344\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/5HmmyPBem70&color1=0xb1b1b1&color2=0xcfcfcf&feature=player_embedded&fs=1\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/5HmmyPBem70&color1=0xb1b1b1&color2=0xcfcfcf&feature=player_embedded&fs=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\"></embed></object>\r\n\r\nIm need the torrent!!!!!!!! ','saint-seiya-anime-im-loved'),(93,'notify-osd on foresightlinux','2009-03-06 02:33:12','Not only on ubuntu its getting the new notify-osd Foresight have implement it... [with some problems](https://issues.foresightlinux.org/browse/FL-1963)\r\n\r\nBut its usable!\r\n\r\n[![img](http://img18.imageshack.us/img18/4159/pantallazodsc.th.png)](http://img18.imageshack.us/img18/4159/pantallazodsc.png)\r\n\r\nits on fl:2-qa label from now ...\r\n\r\n`sudo conary update notify-osd=@fl:2-qa`','notify-osd-foresightlinux'),(94,'imageshack.us client with python powers','2009-03-07 02:50:15','Im searching about the a cli what can i upload images to [imageshack.us](http://imageshack.us) and not found on google....\r\n\r\nSo i write my own client.\r\n\r\n    :::python\r\n    #!/usr/bin/env python\r\n    import urllib2\r\n    from poster.encode import multipart_encode\r\n    from poster.streaminghttp import register_openers\r\n    \r\n    API_URL = \'http://www.imageshack.us/index.php\'\r\n    \r\n    def yesno(x):\r\n        if x:\r\n            return \'yes\'\r\n        else:\r\n            return \'no\'\r\n    \r\n    def upload_file(filename, optsize=None,\r\n                    user_cookie=None,\r\n                    remove_bar=True,\r\n                    tags=None,\r\n                    public=True,\r\n                    ):\r\n        register_openers()\r\n        data = {\'fileupload\' :open(filename),\r\n                \'xml\':yesno(True)\r\n                }\r\n        datagen, headers = multipart_encode(data)\r\n    \r\n        # Some optional parameters\r\n        if optsize:\r\n            data[\'optsize\'] = optsize\r\n        if user_cookie:\r\n            data[\'cookie\'] = user_cookie\r\n        if tags:\r\n            data[\'tags\'] = tags\r\n        \r\n        req = urllib2.Request(API_URL, datagen,headers)\r\n        u = urllib2.urlopen(req)\r\n        return u.read()\r\n    \r\n    if __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n        import sys\r\n        print upload_file(sys.argv[1])\r\n\r\nthe result here:\r\n\r\n![pantallazo](http://img26.imageshack.us/img26/5081/10215948.png)\r\n\r\nThis small app. needs module [poster](http://atlee.ca/software/poster/) what make the encode multipart life easy. (on foresight its on fl:2-devel xD )\r\n\r\nYeah it need more hack .. [hackimages github repo](http://github.com/zodman/hackimages)','imageshackus-client-python-powers'),(95,'vim python support on foresight','2009-03-09 00:27:37','im update few days ago the vim.. on fl:2-devel someone add the params for get the python support im only bake the changes but now i have vim with python powers....\r\n\r\n[![vim](http://img26.imageshack.us/img26/9490/vimsupport.th.png)](http://img26.imageshack.us/img26/9490/vimsupport.png)\r\n\r\nThis because the vim version on conary repo not have support of it. So the rpathians what use ? emacs ? argh!!! ( i dont like)\r\n\r\nthis make the [onmicomplete](http://vimdoc.sourceforge.net/htmldoc/version7.html#new-omni-completion) awesome. and with vim-addons( zodyrepo.rpath.org@rpl:devel ) can be a replace of any IDE.\r\n\r\nSome python code what i learned today [Iterator]:\r\n\r\n    :::python\r\n    In [1]: a = [\"a\",\"b\",\"c\"]\r\n    \r\n    In [2]: b = iter(a)\r\n    \r\n    In [3]: b.next()\r\n    Out[3]: \'a\'\r\n    \r\n    In [4]: b.next()\r\n    Out[4]: \'b\'\r\n    \r\n    In [5]: b.next()\r\n    Out[5]: \'c\'\r\n    \r\n    In [6]: b.next()\r\n    ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n    StopIteration                             Traceback (most recent call last)\r\n    \r\n    /home/zodman/<ipython console> in <module>()\r\n    \r\n    StopIteration: \r\n\r\nIm love python because sometimes not need explains for understand what doing ...','vim-python-support-foresight'),(96,'easygui a module for make easy dialogs with Tk','2009-03-09 14:39:25','Reading the [bucio blog][bucio] at [planetalinux][planetalinux] talking about [zenity][zenity] that remember me the [easygui][easygui] module what think can be solve the same problems of zenity (or not alls ) without the gnome(gtk) deps.\r\n\r\n` python -m easygui `   \r\n\r\n[![easygui](http://img210.imageshack.us/img210/1600/easyguidemo.th.png)](http://img210.imageshack.us/img210/1600/easyguidemo.png)\r\n\r\nSo with it you can make a small dirty tk gui\'s:\r\n\r\n`python -c \"import easygui; easygui.boolbox(\'Are ok\')\" `  \r\n\r\n`python -c \"import easygui; print easygui.ccbox(\'zodman continue\')\" `  \r\n\r\n\r\nfor Foresight users its packaged on fl:2-devel\r\n\r\n` sudo conary update easygui=@fl:2-devel `\r\n\r\n[bucio]:http://bucio.com.mx/\r\n[planetalinux]:http://mx.planetalinux.org/\r\n[easygui]:http://easygui.sourceforge.net/\r\n[zenity]:http://library.gnome.org/users/zenity/stable/index.html.es','easygui-module-make-easy-dialogs-tk'),(97,'xfce 4.6 on foresight linux','2009-03-10 02:49:58','Yeah that its because foresight rulz\r\n\r\n[![xfce4.6][th]][img]\r\n\r\n` sudo conary update group-xfce-core`\r\n\r\nand very happy because this issue fixed [XFCE-37](https://issues.foresightlinux.org/browse/XFCE-37)\r\n\r\n[th]:http://img10.imageshack.us/img10/7492/xfce.th.png\r\n[img]:http://img10.imageshack.us/img10/7492/xfce.png','xfce-46-foresight-linux'),(98,'saint seiya Rocks!!','2009-03-10 03:11:51','are you love saint seiya visit this..... [http://www.elrincondelmanga.com/foro/showpost.php?p=1150573&postcount=436](http://www.elrincondelmanga.com/foro/showpost.php?p=1150573&postcount=436)\r\n\r\nyeah!','saint-seiya-rocks'),(99,'How populate my app Metadata for show on packagekit','2009-03-11 15:09:27','A lot of times people askme that.  \r\n\r\nSo im add the Way for populate Metadata on foresight.packages.  \r\n[https://wiki.foresightlinux.org/display/DEV/set+Metadata+for+package](https://wiki.foresightlinux.org/display/DEV/set+Metadata+for+package)\r\n\r\nAnd a how use the catalog files.  \r\n[https://wiki.foresightlinux.org/display/DEV/Catalog+Files](https://wiki.foresightlinux.